{"word":"πειστέος","slug":"πειστέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πειστέος</b></el> <el>(πειστέος, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:πείθω'><el>πείθω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>one must persuade</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>(from <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>) <i>one must obey</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}